result.name: Kung Fu Dim Sum

reviews.text: Relatively cheap dim sum place. The baked BBQ pork buns are very good. The bun with the runny egg yolk is very sweet and good. Around 144 hkd for 2 people

It's a nice place for dim sum. You can buy each type of item in 1 piece instead of the standard 3 or 4 in a tray. Most of the items are of a good standard. The place tends to be filled up and long queues can be expected during peak periods. Don't expect much in service here as the staff is constantly on the move. The price of one piece of dim sum averages at HKD10. Not expensive for Hong Kong standard.
No next time... Staff handled my orders wrongly and refused to correct . They even change the order form and push it back to me... Their attitude is of my high doubt ...
The food is ok, nothing exceptional. Reasonably priced.
地鐵站口。鋪面大 座卡多，食材新鮮，有選擇，出品企理， 够水準，茶香，價錢平民化 14:30後八折
